  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (85f69d9 2022-05-09T00:04:25.613861+00:00)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nanvil -f https://bsc-dataseed.binance.org\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (M1)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nI used Anvil to fork BSC mainnet from latest block number. No problem when interacting with forked chain, everything was fine, Anvil ran very fast compared to Ganache. But I noticed that my M1 Macbook Air was getting warm when idle. After checking Activity Monitor, I saw that Anvil used 160% CPU when doing nothing.",
